This paper discusses the use of social media data analysis for disaster risk management, which falls under the category of computational science (cs.CY). The paper also mentions the use of advanced analytical techniques, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the filtering and geolocation of tweets, which could fall under computer networks and communications (cs.NI) or security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of socio-economic validation metrics, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) or software engineering (cs.SE).
